<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=5131&amp;p=46490#p46490"><![CDATA[
<div class="quotetitle">Memblers wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent"><br />That is a really cool set, but most of them don't have any spaces between the chars, so they'd run together as tiles.<br /></div><br />The IBM Monochrome Display Adapter had a hack to improve the apparent resolution of text: tiles of 9x14 pixels were stored as 8x14 in the card's ROM. Most tiles had a blank column of pixels added at the right side, except for tiles $C0 through $DF (mostly box drawing tiles) which duplicated the right column of pixels. The 14- and 16-line text modes in EGA and VGA kept the feature.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=9">tepples</a> — Sun May 03, 2009 7:26 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
